  <p class="crumb"><a href="/communities">Communities</a> › <a href="/communities/sagamok">Sagamok Anishnawbek</a> › Long-term care</p>

  <h1>Long-term care: the Espanola MOU and Sagamok</h1>
  <p class="lede">In June 2026 Sagamok joined a regional partnership to explore building a long-term care home near Espanola. The need is real, and so are the questions members have about how the Nation committed to it.</p>

  {% set banner_body %}<strong>Member-compiled and unofficial.</strong> This is a member-compiled summary, not an official communication of Sagamok Anishnawbek or any partner. <a href="/about#corrections">Tell us what we got wrong</a> and we will correct it.{% endset %}
  {% include 'components/notice.html.twig' with { variant: 'caveat', body: banner_body, label: 'About this page' } only %}

  <h2>What was announced</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>On June 26, 2026, Sagamok Anishnawbek, Whitefish River First Nation, the Town of Espanola, and the Espanola Regional Hospital and Health Centre signed a Memorandum of Understanding to explore building a long-term care home for the Espanola and Manitoulin region.</li>
    <li>It is reported as up to 128 beds. The Town of Espanola has committed 19 acres next to the hospital. The hospital would operate the home.</li>
    <li>It is a Memorandum of Understanding to "explore the possibility." The partners say they will now seek provincial and federal support. No timeline has been given.</li>
    <li>The need is real: in Espanola, more than 130 people are waiting for 32 long-term care beds, and families across the region often have to seek care far from home.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why members are asking questions</h2>
  <p>Putting the Nation's name to an agreement is a significant step. Members are asking whether they were informed and had a say before it was signed, and whether the agreement was properly authorized. The public release says members "can expect opportunities to provide input as the project progresses", which raises a fair question about why input would come after the signing rather than before.</p>

  <h2>Questions members are putting to Chief and Council</h2>
  <ul class="ql">
    <li>Who signed the MOU on Sagamok's behalf?</li>
    <li>Did Chief and Council authorize it by resolution, and on what date?</li>
    <li>Were members given full information and a chance to decide before the Nation committed its name?</li>
    <li>What does the MOU guarantee for Sagamok members, in beds, jobs, or a say in the design?</li>
    <li>Why is member input described as coming after the signing instead of before?</li>
  </ul>

  {# Cloudflare Scrape Shield obfuscates email addresses and mailto: links by
