    <p class="or">Or copy and paste this (to political_office@sagamok.ca, subject: Questions about the long-term care MOU):</p>
    <div class="copy">Aanii,

I am a Sagamok member writing about the June 26 Memorandum of Understanding to explore a regional long-term care home (Sagamok, Whitefish River First Nation, the Town of Espanola, and the Espanola Regional Hospital). I am asking:

1. Who signed the MOU on Sagamok's behalf?
2. Did Chief and Council authorize it by resolution, and on what date?
3. Were members given full information and a chance to decide before the Nation committed its name?
4. What does the MOU guarantee for Sagamok members, in beds, jobs, or a say in the design?
5. Why is member input described as coming after the signing instead of before?

Please reply in writing.

Miigwetch,
[your name]</div>
